A tall, powerful wolf stood in the gloom, his back to her. The wall was smeared with blood. The hulking shadow of someone, probably the 
witch, lay crumpled on the floor near the wall.
Frightened, Little Red Riding hood shut her eyes again.
"It is alright now, little girl," The man said, "You can open your eyes."
 She did. The man stood before her, a sprinkle of red on the white part of his shirt against his jacket.
